red a lower age (8.52\nGyr) and a similar total metallicity ([Z/H] = -0.86 dex). Conclusions. Our\nresults indicate that NGC 5044-UCD1 is most likely an extreme GC (MV ~ -12.5\nmag) belonging to the GC system of the elliptical galaxy NGC 5044.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 21 Feb 2017 16:48:14 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-03-08"}
