e effect of\nthe ratio of conducting and insulating areas was also analyzed, and it was\nfound that even for systems with a top plate with only $25\\%$ conducting\nsurface, heat-transport of $60\\%$ of the fully conducting case can be seen.\nChanging the 1D stripe pattern to 2D checkerboard tessellations does not result\nin a significantly different response of the system.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 22 Feb 2017 12:53:10 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 18 Jul 2017 13:02:39 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 20 Sep 2017 13:23:32 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Thu, 21 Sep 2017 14:37:17 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Mon, 9 Oct 2017 11:45:24 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-02-14"}
